messages.message:
Hmm ran into the `extraction failed` issue again on aihub-sandbox (reproduced twice actually), and got both resolved after 1 refresh (or just auto-retry), but this is the console error log I saw both times - `Job response did not contain selected result`.

Though when I compared the results of the two jobs, 1 that triggered `extraction failed` ui and didn't hit `PUT extracted_fields` vs the job that succeeded in displaying fields and hitting `PUT`, there was no notable diff.

But yep, found the error originating from `createJobBatcher` FE logic, where `// if not all (jobs) resolved, the remaining ones are considered errored`
seems like a frontend bug in the batching logic then? @Weiming Wu

Feel free to try adding new files (I did w2) to my project (https://aihub-sandbox.internal.instabase.com/build/0198ec23-fd01-7c93-87ac-b6f65a07f4ca) to reproduce, as that's worked for me the last couple times, but ya, from the network tab I didn't notice many jobs running that would be batched nor failed ones :thinking_rotating:
